Definition: [ἑξακόσιοι] plural ordinal from {{g1803}} and {{g1540}}; six hundred
[ἐξαλείφω] from {{g1537}} and {{g218}}; to smear out, i.e. obliterate (erase tears, figuratively, pardon sin)
[ἐξαίφνης] from {{g1537}} and the base of {{g160}}; of a sudden (unexpectedly) Compare {{g1819}}.
[ἐξακολουθέω] from {{g1537}} and {{g190}}; to follow out, i.e. (figuratively) to imitate, obey, yield to
[ἐξανατέλλω] from {{g1537}} and {{g393}}; to start up out of the ground, i.e. germinate
[ἐξανίστημι] from {{g1537}} and {{g450}}; objectively, to produce, i.e. (figuratively) beget; subjectively, to arise, i.e. (figuratively) object
[ἐξάλλομαι] from {{g1537}} and {{g242}}; to spring forth
[ἐξανάστασις] from {{g1817}}; a rising from death
[ἐξαπατάω] from {{g1537}} and {{g538}}; to seduce wholly
[ἐξάπινα] from {{g1537}} and a derivative of the same as {{g160}}; of a sudden, i.e. unexpectedly Compare {{g1810}}.
[ἐξέραμα] from a comparative of {{g1537}} and a presumed ἐράω (to spue); vomit, i.e. food disgorged
[ἐξέλκω] from {{g1537}} and {{g1670}}; to drag forth, i.e. (figuratively) to entice (to sin)
[ἐξελέγχω] from {{g1537}} and {{g1651}}; to convict fully, i.e. (by implication) to punish
[ἔξειμι] from {{g1537}} and εἶμι (to go); to issue, i.e. leave (a place), escape (to the shore)
[ἐξεγείρω] from {{g1537}} and {{g1453}}; to rouse fully, i.e. (figuratively) to resuscitate (from death), release (from infliction)
[ἐξαυτῆς] from {{g1537}} and the genitive case singular feminine of {{g846}} ({{g5610}} being understood); from that hour, i.e. instantly
[ἐξαστράπτω] from {{g1537}} and {{g797}}; to lighten forth, i.e. (figuratively) to be radiant (of very white garments)
[ἐξαρτίζω] from {{g1537}} and a derivative of {{g739}}; to finish out (time); figuratively, to equip fully (a teacher)
[ἐξαποστέλλω] from {{g1537}} and {{g649}}; to send away forth, i.e. (on a mission) to despatch, or (peremptorily) to dismiss
[ἐξαπορέομαι] middle voice from {{g1537}} and {{g639}}; to be utterly at a loss, i.e. despond

[ἐξουσία] from {{g1832}} (in the sense of ability); privilege, i.e. (subjectively) force, capacity, competency, freedom, or (objectively) mastery (concretely, magistrate, superhuman, potentate, token of control), delegated influence
[ἐξουθενέω] a variation of {{g1847}} and meaning the same
[ἐξορκιστής] from {{g1844}}; one that binds by an oath (or spell), i.e. (by implication) an "exorcist" (conjurer)
[ἐξορκίζω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3726}}; to exact an oath, i.e. conjure
[ἐξουδενόω] from {{g1537}} and a derivative of the neuter of {{g3762}}; to make utterly nothing of, i.e. despise See also {{g1848}}.
[ἐξορύσσω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3736}}; to dig out, i.e. (by extension) to extract (an eye), remove (roofing)
[ἔξοδος] from {{g1537}} and {{g3598}}; an exit, i.e. (figuratively) death
[ἐξισχύω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2480}}; to have full strength, i.e. be entirely competent
[ἐξομολογέω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3670}}; to acknowledge or (by implication, of assent) agree fully
[ἐξολοθρεύω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3645}}; to extirpate
[ἕξις] from {{g2192}}; habit, i.e. (by implication) practice
[ἐξίστημι] from {{g1537}} and {{g2476}}; to put (stand) out of wits, i.e. astound, or (reflexively) become astounded, insane
[ἐξερευνάω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2045}}; to explore (figuratively)
[ἐξέρχομαι] from {{g1537}} and {{g2064}}; to issue (literally or figuratively)

[ἔξεστι] third person singular present indicative of a compound of {{g1537}} and {{g1510}}; so also      ἐξόν neuter present participle of the same (with or without some form of {{g1510}} expressed); impersonally, it is right (through the figurative idea of being out in public)
[ἐξετάζω] from {{g1537}} and ἐτάζω (to examine); to test thoroughly (by questions), i.e. ascertain or interrogate
[ἐξηγέομαι] from {{g1537}} and {{g2233}}; to consider out (aloud), i.e. rehearse, unfold
[ἑξήκοντα] the tenth multiple of {{g1803}}; sixty
[ἑξῆς] from {{g2192}} (in the sense of taking hold of, i.e. adjoining); successive
[ἐξηχέομαι] middle voice from {{g1537}} and {{g2278}}; to "echo" forth, i.e. resound (be generally reported)
[ἑορτάζω] from {{g1859}}; to observe a festival
[ἑορτή] of uncertain affinity; a festival
[ἐξωθέω]   or ἐξώθωfrom {{g1537}} and ὠθέω (to push); to expel; by implication, to propel
[ἐξώτερος] comparative of {{g1854}}; exterior
[ἔξω] adverb from {{g1537}}; out(-side, of doors), literally or figuratively
[ἔξωθεν] from {{g1854}}; external(-ly)
[ἐξυπνίζω] from {{g1853}}; to waken
[ἔξυπνος] from {{g1537}} and {{g5258}}; awake
[ἐξουσιάζω] from {{g1849}}; to control
[ἐξοχή] from a compound of {{g1537}} and {{g2192}} (meaning to stand out); prominence (figuratively)
[ἐπαίρω] from {{g1909}} and {{g142}}; to raise up (literally or figuratively)
[ἔπαινος] from {{g1909}} and the base of {{g134}}; laudation; concretely, a commendable thing
[ἐπάγω] from {{g1909}} and {{g71}}; to superinduce, i.e. inflict (an evil), charge (a crime)
[ἐπάγγελμα] from {{g1861}}; a self-committal (by assurance of conferring some good)
[ἐπαγγέλλω] from {{g1909}} and the base of {{g32}}; to announce upon (reflexively), i.e. (by implication) to engage to do something, to assert something respecting oneself
[ἐπαγγελία] from {{g1861}}; an announcement (for information, assent or pledge; especially a divine assurance of good)
[ἐπαινέω] from {{g1909}} and {{g134}}; to applaud
[Ἐπαίνετος] from {{g1867}}; praised; Epænetus, a Christian
[ἐπαθροίζω] from {{g1909}} and ἀθροίζω (to assemble); to accumulate
[ἐπαγωνίζομαι] from {{g1909}} and {{g75}}; to struggle for
[ἐπέκεινα] from {{g1909}} and (the accusative case plural neuter of) {{g1565}}; upon those parts of, i.e. on the further side of
[Ἐπαφρᾶς] contracted from {{g1891}}; Epaphras, a Christian
[ἐπαυτοφώρῳ] from {{g1909}} and {{g846}} and (the dative case singular of) a derivative of φώρ (a thief); in theft itself, i.e. (by analogy) in actual crime
[ἐπανίσταμαι] middle voice from {{g1909}} and {{g450}}; to stand up on, i.e. (figuratively) to attack
[ἐπανέρχομαι] from {{g1909}} and {{g424}}; to come up on, i.e. return
[ἐπάνω] from {{g1909}} and {{g507}}; up above, i.e. over or on (of place, amount, rank, etc.)
[ἐπανόρθωσις] from a compound of {{g1909}} and {{g461}}; a straightening up again, i.e. (figuratively) rectification (reformation)
[ἐπαρχία] from a compound of {{g1909}} and {{g757}} (meaning a governor of a district, "eparch"); a special region of government, i.e. a Roman præfecture
[ἐπαρκέω] from {{g1909}} and {{g714}}; to avail for, i.e. help
[ἐπαύριον] from {{g1909}} and {{g839}}; occurring on the succeeding day, i.e. ({{g2250}} being implied) to-morrow
[ἔπαυλις] from {{g1909}} and an equivalent of {{g833}}; a hut over the head, i.e. a dwelling
[ἐπακροάομαι] from {{g1909}} and the base of {{g202}}; to listen (intently) to
[ἐπάν] from {{g1909}} and {{g302}}; a particle of indefinite contemporaneousness; whenever, as soon as
[ἐπάναγκες] neuter of a presumed compound of {{g1909}} and {{g318}}; (adverbially) on necessity, i.e. necessarily
[ἐπανάγω] from {{g1909}} and {{g321}}; to lead up on, i.e. (technical) to put out (to sea); (intransitively) to return
[ἐπαισχύνομαι] from {{g1909}} and {{g153}}; to feel shame for something
[ἐπαιτέω] from {{g1909}} and {{g154}}; to ask for
[ἐπακολουθέω] from {{g1909}} and {{g190}}; to accompany
[ἐπακούω] from {{g1909}} and {{g191}}; to hearken (favorably) to
[ἐπαναμιμνήσκω] from {{g1909}} and {{g363}}; to remind of
[ἐπαναπαύομαι] middle voice from {{g1909}} and {{g373}}; to settle on; literally (remain) or figuratively (rely)
[ἐπεισαγωγή] from a compound of {{g1909}} and {{g1521}}; a superintroduction
[ἔπειτα] from {{g1909}} and {{g1534}}; thereafter
[ἐπεγείρω] from {{g1909}} and {{g1453}}; to rouse upon, i.e. (figuratively) to excite against
[ἐπεί] from {{g1909}} and {{g1487}}; thereupon, i.e. since (of time or cause)
[ἐπαφρίζω] from {{g1909}} and {{g875}}; to foam upon, i.e. (figuratively) to exhibit (a vile passion)
[Ἐπαφρόδιτος] from {{g1909}} (in the sense of devoted to) and Ἀφροδίτη (Venus); Epaphroditus, a Christian Compare {{g1889}}.
[ἐπεῖδον] and other moods and persons of the same tense; from {{g1909}} and {{g1492}}; to regard (favorably or otherwise)
[ἐπείπερ] from {{g1893}} and {{g4007}}; since indeed (of cause)
[ἐπειδή] from {{g1893}} and {{g1211}}; since now, i.e. (of time) when, or (of cause) whereas
[ἐπειδήπερ] from {{g1894}} and {{g4007}}; since indeed (of cause)
[ἐνωτίζομαι] middle voice from a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g3775}}; to take in one's ear, i.e. to listen
[ἕξ] a primary numeral; six
[Ἐνώχ] of Hebrew origin ({{h2585}}); Enoch (i.e. Chanok), an antediluvian
[ἐξαγοράζω] from {{g1537}} and {{g59}}; to buy up, i.e. ransom; figuratively, to rescue from loss (improve opportunity)
[ἐξαγγέλλω] from {{g1537}} and the base of {{g32}}; to publish, i.e. celebrate
[ἐξαιρέω] from {{g1537}} and {{g138}}; actively, to tear out; middle voice, to select; figuratively, to release
[ἐξάγω] from {{g1537}} and {{g71}}; to lead forth
[ἐξαιτέομαι] middle voice from {{g1537}} and {{g154}}; to demand (for trial)
[ἐξαίρω] from {{g1537}} and {{g142}}; to remove
